doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    title Delete Account | Flora
    meta(charset="utf-8")
    meta(name="viewport", content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1")
    link(rel="stylesheet", href="/stylesheets/flora.css")
  body
    div.legal-container
      h1 Flora Account Deletion
      p We are sorry to see you go! You have the right to request the deletion of your Flora account and all associated personal data at any time.
      
      h2 Option 1: Delete Inside the App (Fastest)
      p If you still have the Flora app installed, you can instantly delete your account and all data directly through the app settings:
      ol
        li Open the Flora app and log in.
        li Navigate to your Profile.
        li Tap the Settings icon (gear).
        li Scroll to the bottom and tap #[strong "Delete Account"].
        li Confirm your choice. Your data will be erased immediately.

      h2 Option 2: Request Deletion via Web/Email
      p If you no longer have the app installed and do not wish to reinstall it, you can request that we manually delete your account and data.
      ol
        li Send an email to #[a(href="mailto:eporiamusic@gmail.com") eporiamusic@gmail.com].
        li Use the subject line: #[strong "Account Deletion Request - Flora"].
        li Include the email address or phone number associated with your Flora account so we can locate it.
      p We will process your request and confirm the deletion within 7 business days.

      h2 What Data is Deleted and Kept?
      p When you delete your account (either in-app or via email request), we handle your data as follows:
      ul
        li #[strong Data Deleted Immediately:] Your profile details, uploaded photos, voice notes, city/zip code location data, matches, and message history are permanently erased from our active Firebase and Turso databases.
        li #[strong Data Deleted by Third Parties:] Your identity verification status is revoked. Our provider (Didit) handles verification without us storing your documents locally.
        li #[strong Data Retained for Safety:] If your account was previously banned or flagged for violating our Terms of Service (such as harassment), we will permanently retain a one-way hashed version of your email/phone number and your Didit verification status. This is kept strictly to prevent malicious users from creating new accounts and to protect the safety of the Flora community. 

      p For more detailed information, please review our #[a(href="/legal/privacy") Privacy Policy].